As you mentioned you want to have a different `id text` for section rather than a simple number, so i came up with 3 approaches. 

**Option 1 (Not fun):** 
Use a static pattern for the sections

Example:

    &lt;Button
        onClick={((e) =&gt; this.scrollTo(e, `section${i}`))}*
       ....
         }}
         &gt;
        &lt;Tooltip text={tooltipArrayTwo[i]} /&gt;
           {iconArrayTwo[i]}
    &lt;/Button&gt;


**Option 2 (I would use, quick and time saving if i have limited and know sections):**

Array sectionIds = [&#39;sectionId1&#39;, &#39;divisionid2&#39;, &#39;someOtherSection3&#39;];

     &lt;Button
        onClick={((e) =&gt; this.scrollTo(e, `${sectionIds[i]}`))} 
          .....      
         &gt;
        &lt;Tooltip text={tooltipArrayTwo[i]} /&gt;
           {iconArrayTwo[i]}
    &lt;/Button&gt;



**Option 3 (Time consuming and if sections are dynamic/unknown - most fun too):**


mention a specific attribute in each section along with id

/* Returns all the section IDs based on attribute */
function getSectionIds(){
.... logic here
}


      &lt;Button
        onClick={((e) =&gt; this.scrollTo(e, `${getSectionsIds[i]}`))} 
          .....      
         &gt;
        &lt;Tooltip text={tooltipArrayTwo[i]} /&gt;
           {iconArrayTwo[i]}
    &lt;/Button&gt;

Your button can also show dynamic text for each section based on attribute (fully configurable)


**Note:** scrollTo will be a function which uses Js or JQuery for smooth scrolling.



I Hope i was able to give you an approach you can take :-) 


BTW I loved the Menu animation ;-)

